COPY public.country_specific_questions (csq_id, csq_round_id, csq_question_tag, csq_country_name, csq_question_text, csq_language_tag, csq_question_category, csq_country_code) FROM stdin;
3557	3	Elections / Electoral Politics / Opposition / Politics	Botswana	1- Which of the following statements is closest to your view? Statement A: The automatic succession of the Vice President to the Presidency should be changed to allow for an election of a successor; Statement B: The current practice where the Vice President automatically succeeds the President must be retained. 2- Statement A: The current system where Parliament chooses the President should be changed to allow for the direct elections of the President; Statement B: The current system where the President of the country is chosen by Parliament has served Botswana well and should be retain	English	csq 	BW
3558	3	Elections / Electoral Politics / Opposition / Politics	Cape Verde	1- Statement A. The government does a fair distribution of resources among the islands. Statement B. The government favours some islands in detriment of others 2. How do you evaluate the rivalry between badius and sampadjud	English	csq 	CV
3559	3	Local Government	Cape Verde	Do you agree with the creation of the new municipalities?	English	csq 	CV
3560	3	Regionalism (internal/external) / Regional organisations / Multi/Bi-lateral cooperation	Cape Verde	In your opinion, people from these following regions who come to live and work in Cape Verde bring more problems than improvements or contribute to the development of the country? A. Africans B.Asians C.European	English	csq 	CV
3561	3	Other	Cape Verde	In your opinion, do you culturally feel like an African or an European	English	csq 	CV
3562	3	Conflict / Defense / Security / Violence / State Abuse / Vigilantism	Ghana	Which of the following statements is closest to your view? Choose Statement A or Statement B. Statement A: Sexual intercourse without consent should always be considered rape even if it occurs between a husband and wife. Statement B: A man cannot rape his wife because they are married	English	csq 	GH
3563	3	Satisfaction / Trust / Social Grants / Service Delivery	Ghana	How do you rate the overall effectiveness of each of the following governance institutions in the performance of their constitutionally mandated functions, or haven’t heard enough about them?	English	csq 	GH
3564	3	Constitutional ammendments / The Constitution	Kenya	1- Considering the current Constitution and government in Kenya, do you think that the powers of the president are: Too much; About right; Not enough; Don’t know 2- Under the new draft Constitution, do you think that the powers of the president would be: Too much; About right; Not enough; Don’t know 3- What about the powers of the Prime Minister under the new draft Constitution. Would they be: Too much; About right; Not enough; Don’t know 4- Overall, how satisfied are you with the way in which the current government has handled the constitutional review process up to now? 5- In the upcoming referendum in November, will you vote yes to adopt the new Constitution, or no to reject it? 6- If you will vote no, is it because you do not think constitutional reform is needed, or because you are not satisfied with the new draft?	English	csq 	KE
3565	3	Economics	Kenya	1- Have you heard of the Constituency Development Fund? 2- Do you know of any project in your constituency that has been supported by the Constituency Development Fund? [If yes:]If so, did the project benefit the whole community, or just a few individuals?	English	csq 	KE
3566	3	Elections / Electoral Politics / Opposition / Politics	Lesotho	1- In talking to people about elections, we often find that a lot of people were not able to vote in the past Local Government Elections because they were away from home, they were sick, or they just did not have the time. How about you? Did you vote in the Local Government Elections of April 2005? If not, why not? 2- On the whole, how would you rate the freeness and fairness of the Local Government election that were held in April 2005? 3- Which of the following statements is closest to your view? Choose Statement A or B: Statement A- In future local government elections, people should continue to cast only one vote for their preferred candidate. Statement B- Local Government elections should be conducted like those for Parliament. People should cast two votes, one for a candidate and one for a party.	English	csq 	LS
3567	3	Local Government	Lesotho	1- Have you heard of the Local Government? 2- Which of the following statements is closest to your view? Choose Statement A or B. Statement A- The new Local Government System is closer to the people, and will include them in making decisions more than the Central Government. Statement B- The new Local Government will still be controlled by the Central Government, so there will be no change in how decisions are made.	English	csq 	LS
3568	3	Conflict / Defense / Security / Violence / State Abuse / Vigilantism	Malawi	1- In your experience, how often do violent conflicts arise between different social groups in this country? A. Between people of different ethnic groups?\nB. Between people belonging to different religious groups?\nC. Between people of different social groups?\nD. Between people of different political affiliations?\nE. Between Christians and Moslems F. Within your family G. Within the community where you live 2- Looking ahead, do you expect conflicts between different social groups in this country to get better or worse?	English	csq 	MW
3569	3	Satisfaction / Trust / Social Grants / Service Delivery	Malawi	How much would you trust the following to solve a dispute for you or haven’t you heard enough about them to say? A. Family/friends/neighbours\nB. Traditional chiefs/Traditional courts/elders\nC. Religious organizations or leaders\nD. Non-Governmental organizations (including community based)\nE. A vigilante group\nF. Paralegals\nG. Local courts\nH. National courts\nI. The armed forces/police\nJ. Other government agencies\nK. The armed forces of other countries\nL. International mediators\nM. The people involved in the conflict.	English	csq 	MW
3570	3	Corruption	Namibia	Compared to one year ago, would you say corruption in Namibia has increased, decreased or stayed the same?	English	csq 	NA
3571	3	Transitional / Peace processes / Amnesty/ Truth Commissions/ Dialogues	Namibia	In light of the recently discovered mass graves of PLAN fighters, some people have asked for a Truth Commission to talk about the country’s past as a way to promote reconciliation. Others feel that such a Truth Commission is not necessary and that the current policy of reconciliation is sufficient. Please tell us whether or not you PERSONALLY feel such a Truth Commission is needed or not.	English	csq 	NA
3572	3	Constitutional ammendments / The Constitution	Nigeria	Which of the following statements is closest to your view? Choose statement A or Statement B: Statement A. The President of Nigeria should be able to serve as many terms in office as he wishes Statement B. In Nigeria, the President must obey the constitution, including serving no more than two terms in office	English	csq 	NG
3573	3	Land / Natural Resources	Nigeria	Which of the following statements is closest to your view? Choose statement A or Statement B: Statement A. More revenue from oil should go to the communities in the states where oil is produced. Statement B. More revenue from oil should go to the Federal Government for the use of all Nigerians	English	csq 	NG
3574	3	Citizenship / Civil Freedoms (ie. Freedom of speech)	South Africa	Here are some things people say about the way they feel about South Africa. There are no right or wrong answers. We are simply interested in your opinions. Please tell me whether you disagree, neither disagree nor agree, or agree with these statements: a. It makes you proud to be called a South African.\nb. You would want your children to think of themselves as South African\nc. Being South African is a very important part of how you see yourself.\nd. People should realise we are South Africans first, and stop thinking of themselves in terms of the group they belong to.\ne. It is desirable to create one united South African nation out of all the different groups who live in this country.\nf. It is possible to create such a united South African nation.	English	csq 	ZA
3575	3	Regionalism (internal/external) / Regional organisations / Multi/Bi-lateral cooperation	South Africa	1- Have you ever heard anything about the African Peer Review Mechanism (APRM), or haven’t you had a chance to hear or read about this yet? 2- Have you participated in the South African APRM process in any of the following ways? A. Filled out an APRM questionnaire\nB. Attended a public meeting	English	csq 	ZA
3576	3	Elections / Electoral Politics / Opposition / Politics	Tanzania	1- Which of the following statements is closest to your view? Choose statement A or Statement B: Statement A: In elections, candidates should offer gifts to or “treat” voters since this encourages people to vote. This practice should therefore continue; Statement B: Candidates for elected office should never offer gifts to or “treat” voters. This is a corrupt practice that undermines our electoral process and should be discontinued. 2- Statement A: Every citizen must have a right to run for elected office, including independent candidates who are not nominated by any political party; Statement B: Although all citizens have the right to run for elected office, they should first secure the nomination of political party.	English	csq 	TZ
3577	3	Constitutional ammendments / The Constitution	Uganda	Do you agree or disagree with the following proposed amendments to the constitution\nA. Removing Presidential term limits to allow a President to serve more than two terms in office\nB. Ending Special representation in Parliament for social groups such as women and people with disabilities\nC. Ending special representation in parliament for the army\nD. Creating a tier of regional governments	English	csq 	UG
3578	3	Elections / Electoral Politics / Opposition / Politics	Uganda	1- Which is of the following statements is closest to your view? Choose Statement A or Statement B: Statement A. Uganda should move to a political system where political parties can operate freely. Statement B. Uganda should remain with the Movement system, where the activities of political parties are restricted. 2- In your opinion, would a multiparty system be better or worse than the movement system at the following: A. Representing all points of view in government?\nB. Involving people like you in discussions and decision making?\nC. Addressing women issues?\nD. Involving women in government\nE. Promoting national unity.\nF. Ensuring national stability.\nG. Ensuring that people in government do not abuse their power\nH. Observing human rights	English	csq 	UG
3579	3	Elections / Electoral Politics / Opposition / Politics	Zambia	1- Which of the following statements is closest to your view? Choose Statement A or Statement B: Statement A. The best form of government is a government elected by its people. Statement B. The best form of government is a government that gets things done. 2- Statement A. In Zambia today, we now have a real choice among different political parties and candidates Statement B: In Zambia today, we are well on our way to becoming another single party state. 3- In Zambia, is there a difference between a political party and a government, or are they the same thing? 4- In Zambia, is there a difference between the central government and your local government council, or are they the same thing?	English	csq 	ZM
3580	3	Corruption	Benin	Etant donne votre connaissance des organes que je viens de designer, laquelle des affirmations suivantes est plus proche de votre opinion? A: Ces organes ont contribué à l’amélioration du bien être social et à faire reculer la corruption B: Ces organes n’ont pas contribué à ameliorer le bien être social et à faire reculer la corruption	French	csq 	BJ
3581	3	Economics	Benin	A quel point connaissez-vous les organes de contrôle de gestion de l’Etat suivants:? A. Organe d’Audit Interne (DIVI) B. Inspection générale des finances C. Chambre des compt	French	csq 	BJ
3582	3	Citizenship / Civil Freedoms (ie. Freedom of speech)	Mali	Possédez-vous les pièces d’identité suivantes, en cours de validité A. Carte d’identité B. Passeport C. Permis de conduire D. Carte d’électe	French	csq 	ML
3583	3	Elections / Electoral Politics / Opposition / Politics	Mali	Quels sont les plus graves risques sociopolitiques que le Mali pourrait redouter?	French	csq 	ML
3584	3	Elections / Electoral Politics / Opposition / Politics	Senegal	1- Parmi les personnalités suivantes, lesquelles sont susceptibles d’influencer vos choix politiques? A. Guide religieux B. Parents C. Amis D. Ascendants E. Chef de quartier F. Responsable politique local G. Patron, partenaire économique H. Autre (A preciser) 2- A votre avis, pourquoi des gens comme vous s’engagent-ils en politique au Sénégal? A. Pour de l’argent B Pour une meilleure position sociale C. Pour des raisons d’attachement familial ou personnel D. Par conviction politique E. Pour promouvoir le développement du pays ou de leur localité F. Autre (A préciser)	French	csq 	SN
3585	4	Conflict / Security / Violence / State Abuse	Botswana	Thinking of the way media behaves and how the Government responds , which of these three statements is closest to your opinion?\nSTATEMENT 1: The media in Lesotho should be completely free to say whatever it likes about any person in the country. 1\nSTATEMENT 2: Media in Lesotho should be generally free, but with some regulation by Government 2\nSTATEMENT 3: The Government should shut down media that shows no respect for our leaders.	English	csq 	BW
3586	4	Economics	Botswana	Which of the following statements is closest to your view?\nStatement 1: The government should devote resources to keeping our communities clean, even if that means it must reduce expenditure in other sectors such as education and health.\nStatement 2: Keeping our communities clean is a less urgent problem and should therefore not be given any priority over education and health.	English	csq 	BW
3587	4	Education	Botswana	Which of the following statements is closest to your view?\nStatement 1: The government should stick with its new policy of cost recovery in education, which calls for parents who can afford it to pay school fees.\nStatement 2: The old system of free education for all should be reintroduced.	English	csq 	BW
3667	4	Migration / Immigration	Cape Verde	2- Relativamente a cada uma das seguintes declarações, diga-me por favor se discorda ou concorda? A.O Governo trata bem os imigrantes ilegais, dando-lhes o apoio necessário e respeitando os seus direitos. B.Os imigrantes africanos são tratados de forma justa e tolerante pelos cabo-verdianos em geral, e não são vítimas de discriminação.	Portuguese	csq 	CV
3588	4	Elections / Electoral Politics / Opposition / Politics	Botswana	1- Which of the following statements is closest to your view? Statement 1: Mayors of local authorities should be directly elected by the public\nStatement 2: Mayors of our local authorities should be elected by the local government councillors. 2- Statement 1: The automatic succession of the Vice President to the Presidency should be changed to allow for the election of a successor.\nStatement 2: The current practice where the Vice President automatically succeeds the President must be retained. 3- Statement 1: Political parties in Botswana should be publicly funded to put all parties on an equal footing.\nStatement 2: Political parties should continue to be responsible for raising their own funds from their supporters.	English	csq 	BW
3589	4	Foreign influence	Botswana	Many Chinese owned businesses have come to Namibia. How much do you think they have contributed to the development of Namibia?	English	csq 	BW
3590	4	Gender	Botswana	Which of the following statements is closest to your view?\nStatement 1: Women should compete on an equal footing with men in political party primaries to be selected as candidates for parliamentary elections.\nStatement 2: Political party leaders should give preference to women by selecting them as parliamentary candidates for the party’s safest seats or strongholds, instead of holding primaries.	English	csq 	BW
3591	4	Land	Botswana	1-In your experience, how often do violent conflicts arise over land ownership and distribution in Liberia: 2- In your opinion, what is the best way to manage land distribution in Liberia. A-Through inheritance B-By means of purchase at any price set by the owners of land C-By means of purchase at affordable prices set by the national or local government D-Through free distribution by national or local government	English	csq 	BW
3592	4	Citizenship/Identity/social cohesion	Benin	1- Laquelle des affirmations suivantes est la plus proche de votre opinion? Affirmation 1: Je ne voterais pour un candidat du parti politique auquel je me sens le plus proche que s’il venait de mon propre groupe ethnique. Affirmation 2: Je voterais pour un candidat du parti politique auquel je me sens le plus proche, même s’il ne venait pas de mon propre groupe ethnique, mais d’un autre groupe 2- Personnellement, préférez vous ne pas voter pour des candidats d'un certain groupe ethnique?Si oui, de quel groupe ethnique s'agit il?	French	csq 	BJ
3593	4	Corruption/Transparency & Accountability	Benin	1-How well do you know the following state management control bodies?: \nA. Internal audit bodies of ministries (Inspection\nDepartmental General) \nB. Audit Chamber \nC. Inspection Générale des finances \nD. General State Inspectorate \n2-In your opinion, how much have these bodies contributed to the\n improvement of social welfare and the reduction of corruption, or\nHaven’t you heard enough about it?	English	csq 	BJ
3594	4	Local government/ Service delivery	Benin	If we compare the performance of the current administration of President Yayi Boni with that of the previous administration under President Mathieu Kerekou, what do you think of the current administration in the following areas: A. The fight against corruption B. The fight against insecurity C. The fight against the rise in prices D. The relations with the media E. Less with other political forces in Benin G. Public social services (education, health, water and electricity)	English	csq 	BJ
3595	4	Constitution	Burkina Faso	Pursuant to the clause limiting the number of presidential terms, President Blaise Compaoré will no longer be able to stand in 2015 for another term. Would you agree or disagree that the Constitution be changed to allow him to run for a new term?	English	csq 	BF
